><td align="left">0.39*** (0.37***)</td><td align="left">0.32*** (0.40***)</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><hr></hr></td></tr><tr><td align="left">Reality Testing</td><td align="left">0.48*** (0.47***)</td><td align="left">0.38*** (0.42***)</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><hr></hr></td></tr><tr><td align="left">Aggression</td><td align="left">0.34*** (0.32***)</td><td align="left">0.23*** (0.28***)</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><hr></hr></td></tr><tr><td align="left">Moral Value</td><td align="left">0.28*** (0.27***)</td><td align="left">0.26*** (0.33***)</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><hr></hr></td></tr><tr><td align="left">Age</td><td align="left">-0.14**</td><td align="left">0.13**</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><hr></hr></td></tr><tr><td align="left">Gender (men 1: women 2)<sup>a</sup></td><td align="left">0.09</td><td align="left">0.04</td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><hr></hr></td></tr><tr><td align="left">Group (students 1: outpatients 2)</td><td align="left">-0.06</td><td align="left">0.18***</td></tr></tbody></table><table-wrap-foot><p><sup>a</sup>Gender was unknown for one case.</p><p>*<italic>P </italic>&#x0003c; 0.05; **<italic>P </italic>&#x0003c; 0.01; ***<italic>P </italic>&#x0003c; 0.001; parentheses indicate partial correlations controlling for age, gender, and group.</p><p>HAD-A, Hospital Anxiety and Depression Scale-Anxiety; HAD-D, Hospital Anxiety and Depression Scale-Depression.</p></table-wrap-foot></table-wrap></sec><sec><title>IPO subscales and psychological well-being</title><p>The PWB was distributed to the first subset of students (N = 271). As expected, all IPO subscales were significantly negatively correlated with each of the PWB subscales except for non-significant correlations of Autonomy with Primary Defences, Aggression, and Moral Values (Table <xref ref-type="table" rid="T9">9</xref>). All PWB subscales increased with participant age. The above findings were virtually the same even after controlling for the age and gender.</p><table-wrap position